                            <comment id="13575124" author="hustlmsp" created="Sat, 9 Feb 2013 08:58:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;attach the jstack.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13575127" author="hustlmsp" created="Sat, 9 Feb 2013 09:23:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;this race condition is triggered when SyncThread tried to shutdown bookie encountering NoWritableLedgerDirException. the sequence is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) SyncThread -&amp;gt; transitionToReadOnlyMode -&amp;gt; triggerShutDown&lt;br/&gt;
2) triggerShutdown starts a new thread to shutdown bookie. SyncThread joins to wait shutdown thread finished.&lt;br/&gt;
3) Shutdown thread tried to call bookie#shutdown -&amp;gt; SyncThread#shutdown.&lt;br/&gt;
4) SyncThread#shutdown checked flushing flag and found it was in flushing procedure. it doesn&apos;t interrupt SyncThread and just wait.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13575128" author="hustlmsp" created="Sat, 9 Feb 2013 09:32:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;attach a patch to clear flushing flag before trigger shutdown.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
